        </description>
        <description>
          <langstring lang="en">4) Fill in the form.
    (E.g. typing a name for the neuron and pressing 
     &apos;return&apos; 4 times would do the job.)</langstring>
        </description>
        <description>
          <langstring lang="en">5) Now the neuron has appeared in the map,
    you can move it around by drag and drop.</langstring>
        </description>
        <description>
          <langstring lang="en">6) If you want to change the name, add descriptions 
    or some other metadata:
    a) Invoke the menu by right clicking the neuron.
    b) Choose &apos;edit neuron&apos; in the menu. 
    c) Edit whatever you want and don&apos;t forget to press
    the set button for the changes to take effect.</langstring>
        </description>
        <description>
          <langstring lang="en">7) If you don&apos;t save all changes will be lost, the 
    set button only preserves changes during a session.</langstring>
